  <Notes>
    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>In the classification of χαρίζομαι[a] there is obviously a problem of what might be called fuzzy sets, since these meanings may involve not only the transfer of actual objects but may often refer equally well to more generalized activities in which one person treats another graciously and generously (see {D:88.66}). As such, these meanings could very well be classified under certain aspects of Domain 25 Attitudes and Emotions, though there seems to be no clear-cut distinction. Rather, there seems to be a gradient from one aspect of meaning to another.</Content>
    </Note>
    <Note Caller="2" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References>
        <Reference>05700102200028</Reference>
      </References>
      <Content>The form of χαρίζομαι in {S:05700102200028} may best be understood as a passive in contrast with the middle forms of χαρίζομαι which occur with an active sense.</Content>
    </Note>
